<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
McDonnell Douglas: The St. Louis aerospace firm said first-quarter profit 
totaled $2 million, down substantially from the $169-million profit recorded in 
the same period a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue rose 19% to $3.8 billion. The 1989 results included a change in 
accounting rules that added $179 million to the firm's net income. Without that 
change, the 1989 quarter posted a $10-million loss. The firm said gains in its 
combat aircraft segment were offset by a large loss in transport aircraft and 
lower earnings in missiles, space and electronic systems. 
</P>
<P>
Tables, D5 
</P>
</TEXT>
