<HEADLINE>
<P>
ASSESSING A 'FOR ADULTS ONLY' RATING PROPOSAL FOR MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding Jack Mathews' April 12 commentary, "Is It Time to Change the Ratings 
System for Movies?": Perhaps it is time for an A rating (for adults only); but 
after reading his synopsis of the movies he thought needed an A rating, I 
couldn't help but wonder why anyone would want to make those film -- or watch 
them. 
</P>
<P>
What could be entertaining or enlightening about graphic sex, scatological 
violence, child abuse, torture, cannibalism? Do we really need "Tie Me Up, Tie 
Me Down," a movie about bondage? Why not a how-to course too? 
</P>
<P>
MADELINE BAKER, Whittier 
</P>
</TEXT>
