<HEADLINE>
<P>
TICKET AGENCY FEES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Recently I bought two tickets advertised at $21 each to see Midnight Oil at the 
Universal Amphitheatre. 
</P>
<P>
By the time Ticketmaster was through with me, those same tickets cost $28 each. 
For those of you scoring at home, that's a full 33% surcharge. 
</P>
<P>
Consumers need and deserve protection from Ticketmaster and Ticketron, which 
between them control the entertainment ticket industry in our state. 
</P>
<P>
TOM ORTENBERG, Studio City 
</P>
<P>
 A Ticketmaster executive said the charges above the $21 ticket price were: a 
service fee of $4.25; a handling fee of $1.50 per order (in this case, 75 cents 
a ticket); and a facilities surcharge of $2 that went to the Universal 
Amphitheatre. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
