<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BRADLEY SIGNS ORDINANCE TO PROTECT HISTORIC 
ZONE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mayor Tom Bradley signed an ordinance Thursday to protect the historic 
architectural nature of a residential neighborhood north of the Miracle Mile 
shopping district. 
</P>
<P>
"Miracle Mile North is the home of hundreds of irreplaceable examples of the 
architecture that characterized Los Angeles from the mid-1920s to early 1940s," 
City Councilman Zev Yaroslavsky said at a signing ceremony in the neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, the council voted 14 to 0 to approve the ordinance setting 
up the special district in an area bounded by Beverly Boulevard on the north, 
La Brea Avenue on the east, 3rd Street on the south and Gardner Street on the 
west. 
</P>
</TEXT>
