<P>
2 MEDFLIES FOUND OUTSIDE SPRAY AREAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Agriculture officials announced the discovery of two Mediterranean fruit flies 
-- one in the city of Cerritos and the other in the San Bernardino County 
community of Rancho Cucamonga. 
</P>
<P>
The Cerritos fly was trapped Thursday in a fig tree about an eighth of a mile 
outside a treatment area. The Medfly in Rancho Cucamonga was found in a 
grapefruit tree, also just outside a malathion treatment area. 
</P>
<P>
Both flies were identified as immature females. No decision has been made 
whether the areas will be sprayed with malathion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
