<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MALIBU CITYHOOD BACKERS SUE TO BLOCK DELAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Supporters of cityhood for Malibu sued the county Board of Supervisors Friday 
in a bid to prevent the board from delaying the coastal community's 
incorporation if it is approved by voters in June. 
</P>
<P>
The board, under orders from a judge, has set a June 5 cityhood election for 
Malibu. 
</P>
<P>
However, in the same resolution the board included language that would delay 
the actual incorporation for more than nine months after the election, until 
March 28, 1991. 
</P>
<P>
The Superior Court suit filed by the Malibu Committee for Incorporation 
challenged the supervisors' contention they have the jurisdiction and legal 
authority to delay the effective date of incorporation. 
</P>
<P>
Neither the supervisors nor attorneys for the county could be immediately 
reached for comment on the suit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
