<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 122 EVACUATED FROM JET ON RUNWAY AT LAX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A total of 122 passengers were evacuated from a Continental Airlines jetliner 
at Los Angeles International Airport at about noon on Friday after an 
electrical short filled the cockpit with smoke, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The evacuation of the McDonnell-Douglas 80, which had been preparing to leave 
Terminal 6 for a flight to Denver, was orderly and there were no injuries, 
Continental officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Passengers were transferred to another plane to make the flight and the 
jetliner with the electrical problem was repaired within hours, Continental 
said. 
</P>
