<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 3; Column 2; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
71 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NUNN SHOWS NOTHING TO GET EXCITED ABOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michael Nunn is getting a bit too arrogant for his own good. 
</P>
<P>
His reaction to the fans' boos -- "They don't take any punches" -- indicates 
complete disregard for their feelings. One can reply, "He gets paid for it." 
</P>
<P>
Until he defeats someone of the caliber of Sugar Ray Leonard, Tommy Hearns or 
Marvelous Marvin Hagler, let him realize that so far he isn't the second coming 
of Muhammad Ali. 
</P>
<P>
HY GLASS, Sherman Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
