<HEADLINE>
<P>
READERS CONGRATULATE JIM MURRAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a woman who loves sports and reads Jim Murray faithfully, the columns I 
remember most and have saved have nothing to do with sports. 
</P>
<P>
Christmas Day, 1973, on leaving his home in Malibu tugged at my heart. 
</P>
<P>
Then on April 3, 1984, his lovely tribute to Gerry, "She Took the Magic and 
Happy Summer With Her." No one could read it without crying. 
</P>
<P>
Thank you, Mr. Murray, for all the years of reading pleasure you have given to 
sports fans. 
</P>
<P>
JOYCE A. HUNT, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
