<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reebok Tries Again: Reebok is back with its provocative "bungee" jumping 
commercial for its "the Pump" athletic shoes. 
</P>
<P>
That ad, which shows two men leaping from a high bridge with their shoes tied 
to special ropes that are supposed to protect them from hitting the water, 
caused a stir when it first aired last month. Reebok quickly pulled the ad. But 
a new version of it -- with written warnings not to try the stunt -- is airing 
again on CBS and ABC on "selective" programming after 10 p.m, Reebok said in a 
statement. NBC still refuses to air the ad. 
</P>
