<TEXT>
<P>
An appeals panel upheld the suspension of steeplechaser Henry Marsh for failing 
to appear for a drug test. 
</P>
<P>
The Athletics Congress announced April 3 that it would ban the four-time 
Olympian for a two-year period for failing to report in December for year-round 
drug testing. The appeals panel concluded Friday that Marsh had not made 
himself available for testing within 48 hours of receiving notice, as required. 
</P>
