<HEADLINE>
<P>
LONGSHOT WINS FANTASY; HAIL ATLANTIS IS SEVENTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOT SPRINGS, Ark. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Longshot Silvered ran down another longshot, Lonely Girl, in the final strides 
to win the $250,000 Fantasy Stakes Friday at Oaklawn Park, covering the 1 1/16 
miles in 1:44 1/5 on a sloppy track. 
</P>
<P>
Hail Atlantis, part of Wayne Lukas' favored entry with Train Robbery, finished 
seventh. Her stablemate was fourth. Lukas said he would ship Hail Atlantis to 
Churchill Downs and make a decision about her next start in 10 days. 
</P>
<P>
Owned by Arthur B. Hancock III and R.L. Bowen, Silvered returned $52, $19.20 
and $7.40 for finishing a neck in front of Lonely Girl, who paid $11.40 and 
$6.60. Fit to Scout paid $3.80. 
</P>
</TEXT>
