<HEADLINE>
<P>
PICK SIX WINNER COLLECTS $231,875 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One fan collected $231,875.40 with the only ticket with all six winners Friday 
in the Pick Six at Santa Anita, and as a result he may be enjoying retirement 
in the near future. 
</P>
<P>
The 67-year-old building maintenance man who declined to reveal his name, 
employed by an insurance company, selected the winning half-dozen horses by 
name and jockeys, and after purchasing two separate $2 Pick Six tickets he had 
just 50 cents of the money he brought to the track left in his pocket. 
</P>
<P>
'I might give one week's notice at my job,' said the man. 'This is better than 
the $64 I make working for a day.' 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
