<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: YORBA LINDA; 
</P>
<P>
SITE APPROVED FOR COMMUNITY CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LINDA M. HICKMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council this week unanimously approved the southwest corner of Casa 
Loma Avenue and Imperial Highway as the site of a $5.2-million community 
center. 
</P>
<P>
The center, which was proposed in 1987, was originally planned for the grounds 
of the Yorba Linda Middle School. 
</P>
<P>
But after objections from the Placentia Unified School District, the council 
decided to search for another site. 
</P>
<P>
A report by Steve Rudometkin, director of parks and recreation, said the plan 
for the center calls for the expansion of the adjacent Hurless Barton Park onto 
the four-acre site. 
</P>
<P>
Councilman Irwin M. Fried said including the park expansion into the plan "is 
an imaginative, innovative approach." 
</P>
<P>
"This is an exciting project, and I am very pleased with it," Councilman Roland 
E. Bigonger said. 
</P>
<P>
The 26,000-square foot community center is being designed for the use of senior 
citizens, nonprofit organizations, the Yorba Linda Woman's Club and city 
recreation classes. LINDA M. HICKMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
